Jardim, Social Democrats Win Vote in Portugal’s Madeira Region

-- B y   J o a o   L i m a
-- 
2011-10-09T21:30:52Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-09/jardim-social-democrats-win-vote-in-portugal-s-madeira-region.html
Alberto Joao Jardim, president of the
regional government of Madeira, and his  Social Democratic Party 
won elections held today in that Portuguese island region.  The Social Democrats won 49 percent of the vote, and 25 of
the 47 seats in the regional assembly, according to the
Portuguese government’s  election website . The conservative
 People’s Party  won 18 percent of the regional vote and nine
seats.  Jardim has been president of the regional government of
Madeira since 1978.  The region of Madeira had debt of 6.3 billion euros ($8.5
billion) at the end of the first half, Portuguese Finance
Minister Vitor Gaspar said on Sept. 30. Madeira didn’t report
debts or expenses that had a combined impact of 1.2 billion
euros on the 2008, 2009 and 2010 budget deficits, the statistics
institute said on Sept. 30.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Joao Lima at 
 jlima1@bloomberg.net  